meet best practice standards. The Perimeta for 365 service achieves the
following outcomes:

-   Automated deployment of Microsoft 365 environments to a known
    baseline configuration (e.g. DTA Protected Utility)

-   Compliance monitoring of deployed Microsoft 365 environments against
    an established baseline configuration

-   Security configuration comparison against other baselines (e.g. DTA
    Protected Utility, APRA CPS 234)

-   Insights to new features released to existing Microsoft 365 services

Perimeta for 365 can be customised to address specific business
requirements -- ensuring configuration aligns with organisational
objectives, or it can be configured to assess your Microsoft 365
environment for compliance against an industry baseline such as the
Digital Transformation Agency (DTA) Protected Utility for government.
DTA's Protected Utility provides configuration guidance for a secure and
modern desktop, leveraging Microsoft 365 services for government and
critical infrastructure organisations. The DTA Protected Utility
Blueprints were authored by oobe for DTA, in consultation with the
Australian Cyber Security Centre (ACSC), Microsoft and Shearwater.

The Perimeta for 365 service is designed to meet Australian Government
best practice information security requirements. oobe's cyber security
specialists monitor the Perimeta for 365 architecture to ensure it
remains in compliance with the ACSC Information Security Manual (ISM)
and APRA CPS-234 standards.

Perimeta for 365 stores its captured information within Australia in
security compliant regions, and only stores Microsoft 365 configuration
details to be assessed against a secure baseline. oobe's Perimeta for
365 service does not have permission to view or obtain Microsoft 365
corporate data (e.g. documents, records) within a client's tenant, and
has been independently pen-tested by external specialists, and IRAPed
within several projects by multiple clients.

oobe has direct relationships with the Microsoft 365 engineering teams,
ensuring any changes to the underlying cloud platform are known well in
advance, and that policies can be configured accordingly so
organisations such as Austrade are able to maintain the security posture
of its Microsoft 365 environment/s.
